### File Operations API Tests
### Tests for FileOperationsController endpoints
### Self-contained: creates a session for diff endpoint, then cleans up.
### Run requests top-to-bottom.

### 1. Create session (captures sessionId for diff endpoint)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sessions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "agent": "opencode"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("sessionId", response.body.id);
  client.log("Created session: " + response.body.id);
%}

### 2. Get file tree (path is required)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/files/tree?path=.
Content-Type: application/json

> {%
  client.assert(response.status === 200, "File tree should return 200");
  client.log("File tree retrieved");
%}

### 3. Get file tree with path filter
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/files/tree?path=src/main/java
Content-Type: application/json

> {%
  client.assert(response.status === 200, "Filtered tree should return 200");
  client.log("Filtered tree retrieved");
%}

### 4. Get file content
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/files/content?path=pom.xml
Content-Type: application/json

> {%
  client.assert(response.status === 200, "File content should return 200");
  client.log("File content retrieved");
%}

### 5. Search in files (uses 'pattern' param)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/files/search?pattern=OpenCode&path=src
Content-Type: application/json

> {%
  client.assert(response.status === 200, "Search should return 200");
  client.log("Search results: " + response.body.length);
%}

### 6. Find files by name (uses 'query' param, not 'pattern')
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/files/find?query=*.java
Content-Type: application/json

> {%
  client.assert(response.status === 200, "Find should return 200");
  client.log("Files found: " + response.body.length);
%}

### 7. Get file symbols (uses 'query' param, not 'path')
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/files/symbols?query=Main
Content-Type: application/json

> {%
  client.assert(response.status === 200, "Symbols should return 200");
  client.log("Symbols retrieved");
%}

### 8. Get file diff (uses 'sessionId' param, not 'path')
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/files/diff?sessionId={{sessionId}}
Content-Type: application/json

> {%
  client.assert(response.status === 200, "Diff should return 200");
  client.log("Diff retrieved");
%}

### 9. Get file status
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/files/status
Content-Type: application/json

> {%
  client.assert(response.status === 200, "Status should return 200");
  client.log("File status retrieved");
%}

### 10. Delete session (cleanup)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/sessions/{{sessionId}}
Content-Type: application/json

> {%
  client.assert(response.status === 204, "Delete should return 204");
  client.log("Session deleted: " + client.global.get("sessionId"));
  client.global.set("sessionId", "");
%}
